Middle of page, in brown ink by a 19th century hand: Cecilii Firmani Lactancii De Divinis Institucionibus adversus Gentes, Libri VII (Cum Registro); below in pencil: Utdrag ur Flavi Vegeti Renati Epitoma rei militaris libri IV. Om konung Arthur.

binding.p: Modern binding. Leather and paper over cardboard. , stamped in gold: A 215.

history.origin: France , 1472. The watermarks indicate northeastern France, perhaps Troyes. The date is based on the colophon on .
history.provenance: Provenance unknown. The manuscript carries no signa or other marks that can attest to its provenance. It has been at the National Library since the 19th century, as testified by the 19th century binding and the note on .
